# Cloudflare Infrastructure

## Workers

| Worker | Purpose | Trigger |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `greenbrook-framers` | Main app (Next.js) | Custom domain `framers.app` |
| `framers-cron` | Calls `/api/cron` | Cron: `0 17 * * *` (9 AM Pacific) |
| `framers-email-router` | Inbound email forwarding | Email routing rules |
| `tennisrecord-proxy` | Dev-only proxy for tennisrecord.com (bypasses local WiFi block) | HTTP (workers.dev) |

## Secrets (on `greenbrook-framers`)

- `RESEND_API_KEY` — Resend email API key
- `RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET` — Svix signing secret for webhook verification
- `CRON_SECRET` — shared secret between cron worker and `/api/cron` endpoint

`CRON_SECRET` is also set on `framers-cron` worker.

## Bindings (in `wrangler.jsonc`)

- `DB` → D1 database `framers-v2` (id: `8d8cf8ea-3c1b-4019-99d6-64ccf8f71606`)
- `KV` → KV namespace (id: `75842b756f0042a69679be47b6df588b`)
- `ASSETS` → static assets from `.open-next/assets`
- `WORKER_SELF_REFERENCE` → self-referencing service binding

## CloudflareEnv Types

Defined in `src/lib/env.d.ts`. Add new secrets/bindings here to fix TypeScript errors.

## Build & Deploy

```bash
npx opennextjs-cloudflare build          # Next.js → Cloudflare worker bundle
npx wrangler deploy .open-next/worker.js # deploy (reads wrangler.jsonc)
```

Never use `--name` flag — it ignores `wrangler.jsonc` and creates a new worker without secrets.

## D1 Queries from CLI

```bash
npx wrangler d1 execute framers-v2 --remote --command "SELECT ..."
```
